Adrienne Kroell https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adrienne_Kroell 0 Adrienne Kroell (December 13, 1892-2 October 1949), was an American actress. She appeared in over 75 to 90 films between 1909 and 1914. She was born in Chicago, Illinois, United States. She later moved to St. Louis, Missouri and attended Yeatman High School. She first appeared in film in 1909 and appeared in films mostly made by the Selig Polyscope Company until 1914. The Cowboy Millionaire was her first film appearance which also starred Tom Mix. She died at Sturgis Convelescent Home in Evanston, Illinois, of complications from arthritis and was buried at Rosehill Cemetery in Chicago.
